  "datePublished": "2026-03-20",
  "description": "A MacroFocus is a pointed presheaf (H, t*) considered at the fiber level — a RelationalState H with a designated focal history t* ∈ T — whose primary output is the Gurwitsch tripartite field: the theme H_{t*}, the thematic field {H_t : t \u003c t*} of restriction-accessible fibers, and the margin of co-present but inaccessible fibers. MacroFocus is Level 1 of the three-level focus stack: it answers 'which fiber is the current working context' and is the precondition for MesoFocus and MicroFocus.",
  "name": "MacroFocus",
